(WEAR-TV via AP)This photo taken from video provided by WEAR-TV shows emergency responders near the Naval Air Base Station in Pensacola, Fla., Friday, Dec. 6, 2019.
The US Navy is confirming that an active shooter and one other person are dead after gunfire at the Naval Air Station in Pensacola.
The shooter was a member of the Saudi military who was in aviation training at the base, Florida Gov.
The shooting is the second at a U.S. naval base this week.